command to use 


Check Virtualization Support on Ubuntu 20.04

1. Before you begin with installing KVM, check if your CPU supports hardware virtualization:

egrep -c '(vmx|svm)' /proc/cpuinfo
result must be other then 0

sudo kvm-ok
sudo apt install cpu-checker
restart terminal

sudo apt-update
sudo apt install qemu-kvm libvirt-daemon-system libvirt-clients bridge-utils
sudo adduser ‘username’ libvirt
sudo adduser ‘[username]’ kvm
verifier
virsh list --all
sudo systemctl status libvirtd
q to quit
sudo apt install virt-manager
virtual machine handling
sudo systemctl stop libvirtd(arrete tout)
sudo systemctl status libvirtd(etat)
sudo systemctl start libvirtd(demarre)
sudo systemctl enable libvirtd   (permettre au demarrrage)

troobleshoot

systemctl is-active xendomains

sudo systemctl stop xendomains
sudo systemctl disable xendomains
sudo systemctl start libvirtd
